        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 32,
      "start": 301.089,
      "end": 319.121,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "nervous"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "nervous"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "是紧张、担心，常常是因为你不知道接下来会发生什么。考试前、比赛前、老师突然叫你谈话前，都可能 feel nervous。课文里说："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "I felt very nervous when I went into his office."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 33,
      "start": 319.471,
      "end": 322.175,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "afford"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "第二个词："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "afford"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 34,
      "start": 322.525,
      "end": 324.157,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "afford"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "afford"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 35,
      "start": 324.507,
      "end": 341.49,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "afford"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "afford"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "是有足够的钱来支付某样东西。一个家庭可能 cannot afford an expensive toy；一家公司也可能 cannot afford large salaries。课文说："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "The firm could not afford to pay such large salaries."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 36,
      "start": 341.84,
      "end": 344.736,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "interrupt"
      },
      "segments": [
